Corporate Sales Manager
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 05:47:36
Ref. JB3047320
Job Description
The Corporate Sales Manager is responsible for developing the turnover for our French brand; LA CURE GOURMANDE throughout the region, based on predefined objectives and budgets.
Commercial Duties:
Conduct market visits in the region in order to keep all parties informed of key trade and competitor developments
Prepare the yearly budget (internal) and by season according to the previous season sell out
Enter all the related orders in the system
Develop country specific strategies and plans dependent on local market place and the competitive environment
Liaise with the supplier / client
Building long term relationships with the client
Assess monthly the P&L; of the brand ensuring profitability
Ensure that the brand achieve its monthly and annual budgets
Follow up closely all clients’ accounts in terms of ordering, budgets, stock and retail pricing
Solve all problems related to the commercial, logistic and marketing side of the assigned brand (goods to be returned, quality problems, payments…)
Follow up the sales versus targets, versus budget
Follow up of credit collection and overdue invoices settlement
Approach new clients, seeks new accounts and quotes special enquiries to ensure dynamic growth of the brand
Developing sustainable pipelines that results in new account acquisitions
Check and maintains high quality merchandising of all outlets and study the market condition, competition and opportunities
Negotiate current and new proposed point of sales in terms of location, profitability, and exposure and market share
Producing customer specific proposals, attending customer meetings and presentations
Present the new products and collections to customers
Co-operate with the Marketing team.
Prepare and present the weekly/monthly sales reports to the Managing Director
Skills
Sales Management
Key Account Management
